title: Cowboys, Sooners move up 2 places in AP Poll
text:
Cowboys, Sooners move up 2 places in AP Poll UPDATED 2:09 PM CDT Oct 18, 2015 A Large Text Photos 
The Oklahoma State Cowboys and Oklahoma Sooners jumped in The Associated Press Top 25 Poll after this weekend's slate of games. More 
The Pokes (6-0) moved up to No. 14 after their bye week. They were ranked No. 16 in last week's poll. 
Oklahoma (5-1) recovered from its upset against Texas with a 55-0 win against Kansas State in Manhattan, Kan., helping the Sooners jump from No. 19 to No. 17. 
Baylor and TCU remain the only other Big 12 teams to crack the top 25. The Bears (6-0) stayed at No. 2, and the Horned Frogs dropped a spot to No. 4. 
Texas Tech received 14 votes from AP poll voters, but they do not fall within the top 25. 
Ohio State continues to be the top team in the land following its victory over Penn State to improve to 7-0.
